00:44:59.238 --> 00:45:02.430
I know Yoo Jeong Ryeol said he won't get involved in the investigation,

00:45:02.430 --> 00:45:06.263
but the prosecution can't be free from the pressure.

00:45:06.263 --> 00:45:08.407
I'm sure Yoo Jeong Seok knows that too.

00:45:08.407 --> 00:45:12.797
He knows that things will be in his favor if he drags it out.

00:45:13.876 --> 00:45:15.775
And we're almost to the finish line!

00:45:15.775 --> 00:45:19.842
It will be hard to arrest Oh Jong Tae if we can't arrest Yoo Jeong Seok, right?

00:45:19.842 --> 00:45:23.301
I heard the new chief will be coming soon.

00:45:23.301 --> 00:45:25.476
He'll try to control us right away.

00:45:25.476 --> 00:45:29.384
He won't want to do anything that will put him on the superiors' bad side.

00:45:29.384 --> 00:45:32.242
We've sent the subpoena for Yoo Jeong Seok.

00:45:32.242 --> 00:45:34.333
Let's wait for now.

00:45:34.930 --> 00:45:36.764
Will he come?

00:45:41.213 --> 00:45:43.013
Yes, Reporter Jin?

00:45:43.013 --> 00:45:47.355
I'm hungover, so I'm not in the right state of mind.

00:45:47.355 --> 00:45:51.189
I might be saying this because I'm not sober.

00:45:51.189 --> 00:45:52.947
And I might regret it after.

00:45:52.947 --> 00:45:58.411
I might say that everything I said was a lie once I'm completely sober.

00:45:58.411 --> 00:46:02.043
But right now, I think I have to tell you.

00:46:03.360 --> 00:46:05.860
Senior Manager Yoo told me everything.

00:46:08.112 --> 00:46:10.012
Okay.

00:46:10.012 --> 00:46:11.855
Got it.

00:46:13.797 --> 00:46:19.066
Yoo Jeong Seok confessed his crimes to Jin Seo Kyeong.

00:46:20.658 --> 00:46:25.456
He killed both Jo Seong Gi and Jang Jin Soo.

00:46:45.612 --> 00:46:47.812
This is Yoo Jeong Seok.

00:46:47.812 --> 00:46:50.042
Where should I report to?

00:46:52.251 --> 00:46:56.374
Thank you for coming in.

00:46:56.374 --> 00:46:59.589
Please say what you need to before we begin with our questions.

00:46:59.589 --> 00:47:01.580
For your reference,

00:47:01.580 --> 00:47:06.145
we've heard that you've admitted to your crimes.

00:47:07.516 --> 00:47:12.582
You want me to make a confession?

00:47:12.582 --> 00:47:14.727
The detectives should speak through evidence.

00:47:14.727 --> 00:47:17.175
Detectives shouldn't force the suspect to make a confession

00:47:17.175 --> 00:47:19.359
when they haven't obtained evidence.

00:47:19.359 --> 00:47:21.576
You would be neglecting your duty.

00:47:21.576 --> 00:47:23.400
What?

00:47:25.930 --> 00:47:28.530
We'll do the questioning here.

00:47:28.530 --> 00:47:32.098
A journalist is supposed to discover hidden truths.

00:47:32.098 --> 00:47:36.056
Please reveal the truth through the eyes of a journalist

00:47:36.056 --> 00:47:41.114
and tell us what happened when you met with Jo Seong Gi that day

00:47:41.114 --> 00:47:45.192
and what happened to Detective Jang, who was murdered at the same time and place.

00:47:45.192 --> 00:47:47.935
If you hide the truth,

00:47:47.935 --> 00:47:51.446
you would also be neglecting your duties as a journalist.

00:47:51.446 --> 00:47:54.820
A journalist can't reveal the whole truth.

00:47:54.820 --> 00:48:00.767
But I take pride in the fact that I've never lied in my articles as a journalist.

00:48:02.141 --> 00:48:06.665
I will write my story in tomorrow's news.

00:48:07.591 --> 00:48:10.896
You're going to make a confession through your article?

00:48:10.896 --> 00:48:16.487
I will also reveal the truth of what I know about Lee Dae Cheol's case.

00:48:16.487 --> 00:48:20.868
The story will include Oh Jong Tae, the man you want to desperately catch.

00:48:20.868 --> 00:48:24.035
Why do you have to do that?

00:48:24.035 --> 00:48:29.396
I believe I've done many shameful things as a human being.

00:48:29.396 --> 00:48:34.965
But I don't want to do anything that will taint my career as a journalist.

00:48:34.965 --> 00:48:38.965
So he's saying that he admits to his crimes, right?

00:48:38.965 --> 00:48:40.492
I'm not sure.

00:48:40.492 --> 00:48:43.740
I think he might be bluffing.

00:48:43.740 --> 00:48:49.917
So, would it be okay for us to request an arrest warrant and wait?

00:48:49.917 --> 00:48:51.367
I don't intend on running.

00:48:51.367 --> 00:48:55.282
I will be where you can find me.

00:48:56.906 --> 00:49:02.740
Then I'm going to trust your conscience as a journalist

00:49:02.740 --> 00:49:05.125
and wait.

00:49:24.656 --> 00:49:25.956
[Senior Manager Yoo Jeong Seok]

00:49:29.898 --> 00:49:31.598
Hi Senior Manager.

00:49:31.598 --> 00:49:33.842
- Where are you?
- Home.

00:49:33.842 --> 00:49:35.429
You didn't come to the office today?

00:49:35.429 --> 00:49:37.115
I took some time off starting yesterday.

00:49:37.115 --> 00:49:38.968
Come to the office.

00:49:38.968 --> 00:49:42.285
There's one last thing I need to ask you to do.

00:49:42.285 --> 00:49:43.909
Senior Manager.

00:49:44.436 --> 00:49:49.518
I told the police what you told me.

00:49:49.518 --> 00:49:51.524
Come. I'll wait for you.

00:49:51.524 --> 00:49:53.122
Senior Manager.

00:50:20.528 --> 00:50:21.905
Sorry to interrupt your time off.

00:50:21.905 --> 00:50:26.771
As I said earlier, I told the police what you told─

00:50:26.771 --> 00:50:28.379
Don't worry about it.

00:50:28.379 --> 00:50:32.015
I would've done the same if I were you.

00:50:32.015 --> 00:50:35.965
You've done what you should as a journalist.

00:50:35.965 --> 00:50:38.805
If you say that it's not true...

00:50:38.805 --> 00:50:42.335
If you say that you just said it out of anger,

00:50:42.335 --> 00:50:44.874
I will believe you.

00:50:46.257 --> 00:50:48.703
Are you good to write an article right now?

00:50:48.703 --> 00:50:50.290
What could I possibly write right now?

00:50:50.290 --> 00:50:52.481
It's about Lee Dae Cheol's case.

00:50:53.210 --> 00:50:56.010
Lee Dae Cheol was wrongfully executed

00:50:56.010 --> 00:50:58.874
and Yoon Ji Seon's real killer is Oh Jong Tae.

00:50:58.874 --> 00:51:01.358
Write the article with that as the facts.

00:51:01.358 --> 00:51:04.949
I'm going to finally write an article myself too.

00:51:04.949 --> 00:51:09.185
The real killer of Jo Seong Gi and Jang Jin Soo is...

00:51:09.976 --> 00:51:11.908
Yoo Jeong Seok.

00:51:11.908 --> 00:51:15.150
- Senior Manager.
- You know that Oh Jong Tae used me

00:51:15.150 --> 00:51:17.340
to get out of his murder charge, right?

00:51:17.340 --> 00:51:19.186
Include that too.

00:51:19.186 --> 00:51:21.819
You can ask me directly if you need quotes from me.

00:51:21.819 --> 00:51:24.743
Why are you asking me to write this?

00:51:24.743 --> 00:51:26.520
Why?

00:51:26.520 --> 00:51:30.025
If I have to pick a reason...

00:51:30.025 --> 00:51:32.593
It would be to show people one thing.

00:51:32.593 --> 00:51:36.883
That Jeonghan Daily News only reports the truth.

00:51:41.345 --> 00:51:44.094
Okay. I'll write it.

00:52:00.889 --> 00:52:03.830
[The police finally reveal Lee Dae Chul's innocence]

00:52:08.591 --> 00:52:11.969
[I am a Murderer]

00:52:15.595 --> 00:52:18.187
I think we can publish it without editing anything.

00:52:18.187 --> 00:52:19.212
Good work.

00:52:19.212 --> 00:52:21.769
What are you going to do now?

00:52:21.769 --> 00:52:23.780
I feel lighter.

00:52:23.780 --> 00:52:27.825
I felt burdened until now.

00:52:27.825 --> 00:52:29.056
Thanks.

00:52:29.056 --> 00:52:33.251
Thanks to you, I will be able to have a clear conscience as a journalist.

00:52:33.873 --> 00:52:36.498
I still think you wrote this because─

00:52:36.498 --> 00:52:40.683
What? You think I wrote it as a suicide note?

00:52:40.683 --> 00:52:44.019
It was wrong that you killed someone.

00:52:44.019 --> 00:52:48.074
But no one would bravely reveal their crimes like this.

00:52:48.074 --> 00:52:51.332
Please don't think about anything else.

00:52:51.332 --> 00:52:55.338
One of my senior colleagues asked me

00:52:55.338 --> 00:52:59.900
to investigate his death if he's found dead because it has to be murder.

00:52:59.900 --> 00:53:03.371
I'm going to ask you to do the same.

00:53:03.371 --> 00:53:05.419
Why would you ask me that?

00:53:05.419 --> 00:53:10.276
I'm saying I'm not that irresponsible that I would kill myself.

00:53:11.967 --> 00:53:16.527
I believe I still have some work to do.

00:53:16.527 --> 00:53:18.360
Okay.

00:53:18.360 --> 00:53:20.390
I'm going to go now.

00:53:21.810 --> 00:53:23.510
Jin Seo Kyeong.

00:53:24.741 --> 00:53:27.410
During your interview,

00:53:27.410 --> 00:53:31.519
you said you applied to Jeonghan Daily because you wanted to be a journalist like me.

00:53:32.926 --> 00:53:34.526
I'm sorry.

00:53:35.137 --> 00:53:39.960
I couldn't be a role model for you.

00:53:40.896 --> 00:53:43.982
What you've shown me today as a journalist

00:53:43.982 --> 00:53:47.755
I will remember until my last day as a journalist.

00:54:07.915 --> 00:54:11.307
[The police finally reveal Lee Dae Cheol's innocence]

00:54:15.287 --> 00:54:20.013
I told you we can just share one issue!

